.SS CTest Configure Step
.sp
In a CTest Script, the \fBctest_configure()\fP \%<#\:command:ctest_configure> command runs this step.
Arguments to the command may specify some of the step settings.
.sp
Configuration settings include:
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \fBConfigureCommand\fP
Command\-line to launch the software configuration process.
It will be executed in the location specified by the
\fBBuildDirectory\fP setting.
.INDENT 7.0
.IP \(bu 2
CTest Script variable: \fBCTEST_CONFIGURE_COMMAND\fP \%<#\:variable:CTEST_CONFIGURE_COMMAND>
.IP \(bu 2
\fBCTest\fP \%<#\:module:CTest> module variable: \fBCMAKE_COMMAND\fP \%<#\:variable:CMAKE_COMMAND>
followed by \fBPROJECT_SOURCE_DIR\fP \%<#\:variable:PROJECT_SOURCE_DIR>
.UNINDENT
.TP
.B \fBLabelsForSubprojects\fP
Specify a semicolon\-separated list of labels that will be treated as
subprojects. This mapping will be passed on to CDash when configure, test or
build results are submitted.
.INDENT 7.0
.IP \(bu 2
CTest Script variable: \fBCTEST_LABELS_FOR_SUBPROJECTS\fP \%<#\:variable:CTEST_LABELS_FOR_SUBPROJECTS>
.IP \(bu 2
\fBCTest\fP \%<#\:module:CTest> module variable: \fBCTEST_LABELS_FOR_SUBPROJECTS\fP
.UNINDENT
