.B \fBCoverageTool\fP
Added in version 4.4.

.sp
Specify the tool used for collecting coverage during the running
of the tests.  The tool may be one of:
.INDENT 7.0
.TP
.B \fBLLVM\-COV\fP
This value indicates the usage of Clang\(aqs source\-based code coverage
which \(dqoperates on AST and preprocessor information directly\(dq.
For more information, see the Clang Source\-based Code Coverage \%<https://\:clang\:.llvm\:.org/\:docs/\:SourceBasedCodeCoverage\:.html>
documentation.
.sp
CTest will run each test with the \fBLLVM_PROFILE_FILE\fP environment
variable set to \fB<directory>/<test\-name>_<process\-id>.profraw\fP,
where \fB<directory>\fP is the absolute path to the directory where
the \fBCTestTestfile.cmake\fP that describes the test is located.
This configures Clang Source\-based Code Coverage to uniquely identify
the coverage information gathered by each test without any collisions.
.sp
Any existing \fB<directory>/<test\-name>_*.profraw\fP files for a test
are removed before running the test.  Any existing \fBLLVM_PROFILE_FILE\fP
environment variable is ignored.
.UNINDENT
.sp
If no value is specified, no work is done and nothing is added to the
environment.
.INDENT 7.0
.IP \(bu 2
CTest Script variable: \fBCTEST_TEST_COVERAGE_TOOL\fP \%<#\:variable:CTEST_TEST_COVERAGE_TOOL>
